docs.abstract: Race-neutral admissions policies can help further a more multifaceted diversity on America’s college campuses.
docs.snippet: Race-neutral admissions policies can help further a more multifaceted diversity on America’s college campuses.
docs.lead_paragraph: I am the daughter and granddaughter of Indian immigrants. In 1967, my father and grandmother came to the United States from Jhansi, a city in the north of India, to reunite with my grandfather who had arrived three years prior. This was around the time the Civil Rights Act was passed; my grandfather attended graduate school for psychology at DePaul University on a scholarship, with less than $100 in his pocket. In 1995, my mother came to this country, having just married my dad in an arranged marriage. Up to that point, she had never stepped foot on a plane, let alone left India; all she ever knew was in Kanpur.

headline.main: Affirmative Action Is Wrong. There’s a Better Way to Make Campuses Diverse.

docs.abstract: New data shows that the number of abortions fell by more than 10,000.
docs.snippet: New data shows that the number of abortions fell by more than 10,000.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the first two months after the Supreme Court overturned Roe v. Wade on June 24, legal abortions nationwide declined by more than 10,000, a drop of about 6 percent, according to the first attempt at a nationwide count of abortions since the decision.

headline.main: Legal Abortions Fell Around 6 Percent in Two Months After End of Roe
